         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">4/12/69 ¶  ¶ I am very much pleased, dear Dr Hooker, that the ponderous Todea reached Kew in safety and was so welcome to you. ¶  It is certainly an attractive feature in any fern-collection &amp; a singu...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">69.12.04a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70, ff. 410-11.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation: 'And March 2[9]'. See J. Hooker to M, 28 March 1870 (in this edition as 70-03-28b).</p>
               </note>4/12/69</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am very much pleased, dear Dr Hooker, that the ponderous <name key="Todea">Todea</name> reached Kew in safety and was so welcome to you.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See J. Hooker to M, 10 September 1869.</p>
               </note> It is certainly an attractive feature in any fern-collection &amp; a singularly peculiar one too. The tender Hymenophylla can be well grown on the stems, and <name key="Chiloglottis%20Gunnii">Chiloglottis Gunnii</name> is prone to nest in it. No vernacular name exists for this fern, but in my Exhibition Essays &amp; other writings I called this large <name key="Todea">Todea</name> the "Square fern", its stem being often as broad as high. I can send you several yet of similar size, if you can utilize them for interchanges. We have adopted here sawdust for packing ferntrees, <name key="Zamia">Zamia</name>s &amp;c with great success.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will gladly send you the <name key="Alsophilae">Alsophilae</name> &amp;c as you desire.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>But see J. Hooker to M, 14 May 1869.</p>
               </note> For the <name key="Bromeliae">Bromeliae</name> &amp;c I shall feel very deeply indebted and I hope you will succeed also with the transfer of a <name key="Dionaea">Dionaea</name> to Australia.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <name key="Xanthorrhoea%20minor">Xanthorrhoea minor</name> wants heath soil. I have no doubt it will push forth its flowers in due time.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>specimen sent by M 'some years ago' flowered at Kew in February 1877 and was figured in Hooker (1865-1904), vol. 103, t. 6297.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>One of your last letters was written by a Lady's hand. I suppose it is written by an accomplished daughter of yours or by the learned Mrs Hooker.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>All the surviving letters from this period are in Joseph Hooker's hand.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The palms from Lord Howe's Island are all <name key="Kentia">Kentia</name>s, as far as I can see from the scanty material at present &amp; to this genus Blume already many years ago referred <name key="Areca%20sapida">Areca sapida</name>. I overlooked this when I wrote my sketch of the vegetation of the Chatham Islands.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B64.10.02, p. 55.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Many thanks for the photograms from Kew. You must produce a marvellous effect by the varied Tropical vegetation in your expansive houses.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See J. Hooker to M, 10 September 1869.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The plants pr Essex came mostly in excellent condition and the majority is new to Australian Horticulture So I feel truly grateful for them</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have asked Mr Baker to compare kindly one or two ferns in your great storehouse of dried plants<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Request not found.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With kindest regards</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Private</hi>
               </seg>:</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">It was intended to encroach on my administrative position; but I defended my dignity &amp; have been, as far as yet apparent, completely victorious.<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hooker thought that M was unfit for the practical working of the Botanic Garden and that 'he would be wiser to [have] a skilled Superintendent to direct the practical Horticulture' (J. Hooker to H. Barkly, 17 March 1870,  RBG Kew, archives, Letters from Joseph Hooker, vol. Ada-Bar, ff. 180-3 (MS is a typescript copy of unknown provenance)).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
